##Vice Director of Statistics Bureau of Hubei Province gives live lecture

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Reporter for the paper, Wang Xuanhui, intern, Zheng Xu

Ye Qing, deputy director of the Statistics Bureau of Hubei Province, described the impact as "unprecedented" . He told thepaper.cn that it was on the night of January 20, when academician Zhong Nanshan said the virus would be "transmitted from person to person, " that people around him, including himself, realized the seriousness of the outbreak.

"since then, some measures related to the epidemic have been slowly implemented... This is the biggest event I have experienced in the 40 years since I came to Wuhan. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ye Qing. Images are from Ye Qing's Weibo.

Ye Qing kept a journal, writing about his experiences at work and commenting on current events almost every day. During the epidemic, he will be in Wuhan to see and hear what he wrote a "epidemic diary. ". The diary contains his reflections on the phenomena around him, as well as economic data analysis in the form of epidemics.

He also made 16 recommendations to relevant authorities on the epidemic situation, including one provincial and municipal support for a prefecture and city in Hubei Province, and the need to conduct temperature measurements when entering medium and large supermarkets, many of these recommendations are in line with measures currently being implemented by the government.

"We have a lot to learn from this epidemic and a lot to change, " Ye Qing said, suggesting that after the outbreak, a national health campaign would be launched every Saturday to encourage civil servants and citizens to participate at least once a month.

The outbreak has had a huge impact on businesses, and Ye Qing has given lectures to entrepreneurs, including live, to help them answer questions about national policies. He believes that in the face of the epidemic to rely on one, two rely on the government, the government's support policies for small and medium-sized enterprises, the use of good policies to help themselves out of trouble. He predicted that there would be "retaliatory" economic growth after the outbreak ended.

A huge change in your life and work

Until Feb. 14, Ye Qing's neighborhood will be able to send one person per family for three days with a ticket to buy groceries and food. But after the 14th, residents were no longer allowed in and out of the neighborhood. "Now we buy things on the Internet, couriers put them at the gate of the community and we go down and get them ourselves, so as to minimize human contact, " Ye Qing said.

With the development of the epidemic, the factories in Hubei Province also all stopped working. Originally, according to the notice, they were to resume work on February 14, but because the situation was still serious, on February 13, the Government of the People's Republic of China issued a notice, all enterprises in the province will resume work no earlier than 24:00 on February 20, with the exception of those related to the prevention and control of the epidemic, the operation of public utilities, the living needs of the masses and other relevant enterprises that involve the vital national economy and the people's livelihood.

On Feb. 14, Ye Qing began working online, where all three of his departments communicate and hand over jobs.

Now he gets up in the morning and reads a lot of news and material from that day and yesterday. He starts to keep a diary at noon. In the evening, he also does a live broadcast for entrepreneurs in a group of entrepreneurs and gives them some advice. "especially during the epidemic period, small and medium-sized enterprises are not having a good time, so I have to interpret some policies of the state and Hubei on small and medium-sized enterprises for them to calm their hearts and minds, " Ye Qing said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ye Qing on the live platform for entrepreneurs, Internet users to do policy interpretation.

On February 8, the General Office of the Hubei Provincial Government issued the notice on policies and measures to deal with the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic and support msmes to tide over the difficulties, from the enterprise to reduce the burden, strengthen financial support, increase financial and tax support, increase the stability of the four aspects of support to introduce 18 measures. What Ye Qing has done is to read 18 policies one by one for small and medium-sized entrepreneurs. "If any entrepreneur has any questions about that policy, I'll pick them out and explain them in detail. "

It is because of these daily work, even if stay at home, he still every day "too busy" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the meantime, Ye Qing has made a number of recommendations related to the outbreak.

Keep a diary of the epidemic situation and give advice

Usually, Ye Qing has a habit of writing articles and keeping a diary. He has his own wechat account, and a look inside the article can see a lot of "Ye Qing looked at finance" , "Ye Qing looked at data" and other articles he usually wrote columns and diaries.

Ye Qing began writing about the outbreak on Jan. 22, and has since written more than 20 entries. His Journal contains his thoughts on some phenomena, economic data in the form of epidemics, and his advice. As an economist, he also cites a number of economic phenomena, and believes there will be "retaliatory" consumption after April.

"Xx Day, the country newly confirmed cases... " every day of the epidemic diary, Ye Qing always first focus on some of the epidemic data that day, followed by some of the recent and that day's events and some of the central government's policy evaluation. For better or worse, Ye Qing had an opinion.

In addition to this, Ye Qing also gives his own advice in his journal. In his diary, Ye Qing noted the many public health problems caused by the outbreak. He believes that in public health security, first of all, the leadership at all levels to enhance health awareness, medical experts-type cadres, can assume the deputy at all levels, in charge of health care; Non-medical graduates at all levels of the Health Commission director to professional institutions to study half a year before taking up their posts; all levels of government to hire experts, the formation of economic development, investment committee.

He also thinks the country could adopt a rule that calls for a public health and safety day every Saturday to disinfect and clean up workplaces. "The rapid outbreak has a lot to do with inadequate routine disinfection. "

Another very important function of the United Front Ye Qing is to give advice. During the epidemic, he gave 16 pieces of advice, many of which were based on his observations of life.

On January 27, he and his wife wore masks to the supermarket to purchase supplies, to see two 3-4-year-old children sitting in a shopping cart, the mother pushed shopping, although the child wore masks, but the nostrils, mouth are exposed. Walking in front of the supermarket, he found that there were no artificial or intelligent thermometers and people in line to pay too close to the door.

He wrote advice on the phenomenon. He believes that small supermarkets should have manual thermometers, medium-sized supermarkets above should have like high-speed railway stations, subway stations like the intelligent thermometers; try to package sales; promote online food market and other recommendations. According to Ye Qing's own life experience, some of the recommendations are slowly being implemented and implemented.

"I'm a Democrat, it's my job to give advice, and when I see a problem, I have to bring it up, " Ye Qing said.

"still optimistic about the economy. "

In Ye Qing's diary, there is much analysis of the economic situation. Ye Qing believes that the big picture depends on the location of Hubei and Wuhan Advantage, overall will not be too much impact, but for economic growth and some small businesses hit more.

"If you compare the economic changes during the SARS period, you can see that the economic growth rate in the first quarter is likely to be lower, " Ye Qing said, ye Qing believes there will be a "retaliatory" spending in the economy in the second quarter.

"Academician Zhong Nanshan said that this epidemic may be over or better by April, so I think there may be 'retaliatory' economic growth in April, " Ye Qing said, pent-up consumption due to the epidemic will break out after the epidemic, and some people who haven't been out for a long time will start spending, which will then drive the economic recovery, "during the SARS period, there was a slowdown in the second quarter, but there was also a 'retaliatory' growth in the third quarter. "

But in the face of "retaliatory" consumption, Ye Qing feels the need for more attention to hygiene. "people will regroup in the face of the economic recovery, sanitation must be done in places with large numbers of people, and restaurants should adjust their tables appropriately so that they are not too close to the tables, " he said

Ye Qing's bullish view of the economy is also based on his observations of the stock market. in Ye Qing's diary, on February 3rd, about $10 billion of insurance money was already in the market. A number of big insurers have also issued internal instructions to equity managers: No net sales on Monday. Large insurance institutions agree that the long-term trend of a shares does not change due to short-term shocks, the Shanghai Composite Index Below 2800 points is a good buy for long-term investors.

He believes that this phenomenon is to illustrate the epidemic during the stock market and listed companies to the power. "I think the stock market data will go down in history as well as the epidemic data. "

Compared with large enterprises with abundant capital, small and medium-sized enterprises face a more severe dilemma. In response, Ye Qing said, the government introduced a policy of reducing costs, cutting taxes and exemptions, supporting capital, employment and other four major policies. "especially for some companies that produce masks, the policy is to increase the salary of the mask-maker by five times and the management by three times. Some companies may not be able to afford it, and then the government will subsidize it, " he said, with government subsidies, the overall economic situation will be maintained at a relatively stable level.

He also suggested that some small and medium-sized enterprises, in the face of the epidemic to do one on their own, to reduce costs and stabilize workers; and two rely on the government, to pay attention to the government's support policies for small and medium-sized enterprises, to use good policies to help themselves out of difficulties.

At the same time, Ye Qing said, this outbreak will bring about a series of industrial changes, in this epidemic, a large number of voice control and artificial products put into use, for example, the first disinfection robot in the Sixth Hospital of Wuhan played its good effect during the epidemic prevention. In the future, hospitals, airports, shopping malls, train stations, bus stations, wharves, administrative centers, crowd centers, homes and so on will all use more and more high-tech robots to sterilize and connect to the Internet, this is bound to bring a series of business opportunities.

"The time has come for companies that produce air purifier to upgrade to producing sterilised robots, " Ye Qing said. "With the new pneumonia, China's big health industry will grow rapidly. ".

Ye Qing's 16 tips for dealing with new coronary pneumonia

1. Suggestions for strengthening supermarket management
One is that small supermarkets should have manual thermometers, and medium-sized supermarkets above should have intelligent thermometers like high-speed railway stations and subway stations.

Second, under the age of 10,70 years old, pregnant women in the "new pneumonia" period do not go to the supermarket and other places. And control the number of people in the store.

Third, in addition to the mask, the proposal to wear disposable gloves, shoe covers. Because the selection, the opening, the payment and so on all must touch the article or the handle.

Four is to pay a distance of one meter. The same is true of banks, airports, and supermarkets.

Five is the used mask, disposable gloves, put on the door of the special bag, coat pants on the balcony, shoes do not enter the house.

Six is to promote online vegetable market.

Seven is to adjust the weighing operator and weighing system. It's the vegetable section where the weigh-in is busy, and the fruit and meat section where the weigh-in is not. Suggest a link. Should all be ready to be weighed.

Eight is to try to package sales, package the vegetables in advance, weighed well, took the direct payment. Cut Down on the time it takes to line up for the weigh-in.

Nine is to use Wechat, alipay and other self-service billing system.

Ten is the shelf adjustment in the supermarket.

2. Emergency advice on baby care

Due to the closing of some shops, not only the supplies for adults are tight, but also the supplies for small people are tight. The Hubei Mother and Child Association recommends:

(1) respond positively, arouse the attention of the whole society, as soon as possible baby supplies (especially milk powder and other products that are just needed) into the people's livelihood materials.

(2) to provide strict protective measures for mother and baby stores and shop assistants who are able to operate and deliver goods to their homes.

(3) consumers in the hardest-hit areas cherish the logistics resources and epidemic prevention resources that the government and the whole society have squeezed out for just-needed products for mothers and babies. Under the guidance of professionals, they can purchase the goods in one lump sum, store the goods in a reasonable lump sum, and reduce the number of times of distribution, reduce the risk of infection among employees.

(4) in other areas where the epidemic is not yet serious, due to the ease of logistics and distribution, vigilance should be exercised. Young parents should stock up in advance and stock up on enough food to completely eliminate the risk of food shortage for their babies.

3. Advice on opening a traditional Chinese medicine store

Suggest that the whole country's traditional Chinese medicine shops, like supermarkets, all open.

4. A proposal to launch a national clean up campaign every Saturday morning

The biggest lesson of the new type of pneumonia is to maintain a healthy lifestyle and a good living environment. In the case of environmental protection work is taken seriously, there should be no corner to keep the living environment clean.

It is recommended that a national health campaign be launched every Saturday after the outbreak. Civil Servants and members of the public are encouraged to participate at least once a month.

5. Advice on not wearing N95 masks in the civil service

On television, some public officials, including leading officials, are wearing general medical surgical masks, as well as leading by example, and do not wear N95 masks. Give priority to the first-line medical staff, public security, traffic, grid screening personnel, they contact more people, contact suspected, confirmed patients, need to strengthen protection. It is recommended that these two approaches be replicated throughout the country.

6. The Civil Affairs Department pays attention to the suggestion of "the sunshine clan" 

At present, in addition to patients, medical staff, community cadres, but also pay attention to low-income, no income of the homeless. I call these people the solariums. That's money, that's money, that's money. He worked as a rag-picker and day-laborer to meet his daily expenses. Used to be able to scrape by. And now there's nothing to be done.

It is suggested that civil affairs departments at all levels should pay attention to and settle down.

7. Emergency advice from a provincial and municipal medical team to assist a prefecture-level city in Hubei Province

Can the State Council issue a regulation, so that the conditions of the provinces and cities to send medical teams to support a fixed city. Including personnel and supplies. The Sichuan earthquake was one such aid.

8. Suggest recruiting volunteers to fill the Red Cross, Charity Federation

At present, the Red Cross Societies and charity associations at all levels are very busy. In addition to allocating funds, a large number of items can not be delivered to hospitals, and some Red Cross societies are looking for volunteers, including people with cars. It is recommended that volunteers be activated to augment the above-mentioned institutions.

9. Taking care of the people of Wuhan while they are away also helps Wuhan

At this time, the Wuhan people living outside good or not?

You can imagine how hard it must have been. From the 26th, the topic of how Wuhan People Go home flooded wechat. The people of Wuhan in Han Dynasty will certainly understand the people of Wuhan outside. Yesterday I said to be kind to Wuhan people. It seems that this is a matter that needs the help of the whole nation.

10. Develop Recommendations for medical personnel to report any possible clues to the outbreak

Doctors are the most sensitive to outbreaks. The state should establish a mechanism to direct suspected infectious diseases to the CDC of the State Council, and send a national-level expert group directly from the CDC to study and confirm if a report is received, and form a rapid response. Too many mistakes have been made in the middle links, it's better to be sure it's not contagious than to wait for it to happen.

Therefore, I suggest that in the future, a system should be put in place to allow medical personnel to report any possible clues to the outbreak in a timely manner.

11. Train officials at all levels to improve their ability to respond to public opinion

In the face of unexpected events, the most effective way is to apologize first.

In the Internet Age, there are three main points for government officials to deal with emergencies:

1) tell the truth and only the truth, and be careful of the facts.
2) zero rejections and, if possible, all the bad news at once.
3) learn to apologize, lower expectations, and don't talk big.

Therefore, I suggest that cadres at all levels to deal with the new media training courses. This is a very important quality for cadres.

12. Suggestions for adding foldout beds to donations

Can I donate a foldout bed to the hospital?

Whatever is missing on the medical front, we will support.

13. Combine home isolation with centralized isolation

On February 2, Wuhan issued notice No. 10, requiring all urban areas of the city to carry out "four categories of personnel" centralized admission and isolation work.

The four categories of people are: confirmed patients, suspected patients, fever patients who can not rule out infection, close contacts of confirmed patients.

Well, that's something to fight COVID-19 pneumonia on. That was the case with SARS. It is recommended that all localities also adopt this approach, combining designated hospitals, centralized isolation and home isolation. Avoid Wuhan's detours.

14. The Director of the Health Commission shall be trained for more than half a year

It's a terrible thing to be the director of the Health Care Commission... and not understand basic medicine.

Huanggang City Health Commission Director "one question three do not know" , is a case. How many other directors of the Health Commission in the country are so ignorant of medicine. Therefore, it is suggested that non-medical graduates at all levels should study for half a year before taking up their posts.

15. Tips on how to run an online trade show

Under the influence of the new type of pneumonia, all over the announcement of the suspension of various exhibitions. The impact on the economy is very direct.

Then our various exhibitions should also be moved to the Internet, long-term online exhibitions. This will keep the library open for 365 days, and you can order 24 hours a day.

16. Recommendations for Integrating National Health Security into the work of the centres

Through this "new coronary pneumonia" , it is suggested that the national health security as the focus of work. This is a rational extension of governance. It is suggested that economic development and environmental protection should be promoted to health protection.
